<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFBFFBAFC959DF76C287FC6" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC959DF76C327F6B" blockId="22.[831,1436,435,679]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC959DF76ABD7CAA" bold="true" box="[831,944,435,459]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species differs from the previous one by having higher elongated ridges but they are interrupted at the sutures which are not raised or tuberculated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFBFFBAFC959E556C287FC6" blockId="22.[831,1436,435,679]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFC959E556D7E7F48" bold="true" box="[831,1139,529,553]" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It is recorded in the Esna Shale of Wadi Mellaha and 
<collectingRegion id="8818F811FFFBFFBAFBD09E756DB67F29" box="[1146,1211,561,584]" country="Egypt" name="Al Uqsur" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Luxor</collectingRegion>
areas by NAKKADY (1950). It is found in the top part of the Esna Shale 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFCEA9E346A457FE9" box="[832,840,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">(</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFBFFBAFCED9E346DB07FE6" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" box="[839,1213,624,648]" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="velascoensis">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFCED9E346D607FE9" box="[839,1133,624,648]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Morozovella velascoensis</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DDC4D70FFFBFFBAFABC9E346AFE7FC6" authority="Zone" authorityName="Zone" class="Globothalamea" family="Truncorotaloididae" genus="Morozovella" kingdom="Chromista" order="Rotaliida" pageId="22" pageNumber="36" phylum="Foraminifera" rank="species" species="subbotinae">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFBFFBAFABC9E346AB87FC6" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="36">Morozovella subbotinae</emphasis>
Zone
</taxonomicName>
) of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
